Disk usage
df and du

df
	stands for disk free means gives info about space available in disk
1st	shows the file system path. the important one is nvmexxx it shows how
	much space it totally have


-h	human readable format
-T	type format
-x var	to exclude something like ignore

drawback	It doesn't show how much space is actually used by a 
		directory

du
	we can specify the path with du so it shows the actuall space used
	used inside that directory

-h	human readable format
-s	summary 
-c	gives total
--max-depth=value	how much deep it can go. whether it should go 1 folder
			or upto given value

drawback	It floods the terminal with files
